    • Method Detail

      • getDistanceFromLocationKey

        public double getDistanceFromLocationKey(double locKey)
        Computes the circular distance between the running FPeer this location key and the passed location key.
        Parameters:
        locKey - the location key to compare with the running FPeer's location key
        Returns:
        min (abs(this.locKey - locKey), 1 - abs(this.locKey - locKey))

      • equals

        public boolean equals(java.lang.Object peer)
        Compares the passed FPeer p with the FPeer this, via address-comparison. In other words, two FPeers are equals if they are the same object.
        Overrides:
        equals in class java.lang.Object
        Parameters:
        peer - the FPeer to compare with the FPeer this
        Returns:
        true if the two FPeers are equals. false otherwise.

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(FPeer p)
        Compares the passed FPeer p with the FPeer this, via location keys comparison.
        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<FPeer>
        Parameters:
        p - the FPeer to be compared with this
        Returns:

      • swapWith

        public void swapWith(FPeer fpeer,
            int linkablePID)
        Performs the swap of the location key and of the stored content location keys of the running FPeer with the relative fields of the passed FPeer fpeer. Furthermore, updates the neighbor's trees neighborhood representation with the new locations-changed FPeers. This last operation is needed to maintains the trees sorted by FPeer's location keys and ensure O(logN) operations on its.
        Parameters:
        fpeer - the FPeer with which perform the swap
        linkablePID - the protocol identifier of the Linkable protocol used during the simulation
